                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On February 25 the won settlement negotiations were ostensibly concluded. The
                    total amount agreed upon was $85,800,000 in payment for all won drawings through
                    February 6, 1953 ($82,800,000 for won drawings prior to December 16, 1952, and
                    $3 million for drawings since that time up to February 6 at the rate of 18,000
                    won to the dollar). As of February 26, the Republic of Korea converted its
                    currency from won to hwan. Beginning February 25, the United Nations Command
                    bought hwan at the rate of 180 to the dollar, and under the terms of the
                    agreement, the rate would be adjusted April 30 and every three months thereafter
                    based upon changes in the Pusan wholesale price index. (Memorandum by <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRJG1">McClurkin</persName>, February 25, 1953;
                    895B.131/2–2553)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
